The paper deals with the problem of synchronization in networked systems, which is a core topic in the field of control systems (cs.SY). The application of the results to secondary voltage pinning control design for a microgrid suggests that the paper may also fall under the sub-category of cyber-physical systems (cs.SI). The use of polynomial complexity algorithms and bounds on algebraic connectivity suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of distributed computing (cs.DC) and electronic engineering (cs.ET). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of physics and society (cs.PF) due to its potential impact on the efficient and effective operation of power microgrids.
